Y'all, this our simple PHP tutorial go show you how to fetch and display today's date for your webpage. Use this our code snippet below:

```php
<?php
  // Get today's date
  $today = date("l, F jS Y");
  $greeting = "Today na " . $today . ", enjoy your day!";
  echo $greeting;
?>
```

Copy this code inside your HTML file, save am as .php, then open am for your browser. Y'all go see the date display well well with a nice greeting message.
